104static inline uint8_t mult(uint8_t a, uint8_t b)
105{
106 if(a == 0 || b == 0)
107 return 0;
108 return ALOG[(LOG[a] + LOG[b]) % 255];
109}
110
111static void CreateECCBlock(ByteArray& data, int codeOffset, int codeLength, int eccOffset, int eccLength, int stride)
112{
113 // binary search for the poly vector with length numECWords
114 auto iter = std::lower_bound(FACTORS.begin(), FACTORS.end(), eccLength,
115 [](const ByteArray& vec, size_t size) { return vec.size() < size; });
116 if (iter == FACTORS.end())
117 throw std::invalid_argument("Illegal number of error correction codewords specified: " + std::to_string(eccLength));
118
119 auto& poly = *iter;
120 ByteArray ecc(eccLength);
121 for (int i = 0; i < codeLength; ++i) {
122 const auto m = ecc.back() ^ data[codeOffset + i * stride];
123 for (size_t k = ecc.size() - 1; k > 0; k--)
124 ecc[k] = ecc[k - 1] ^ mult(m, poly[k]);
125 ecc[0] = mult(m, poly[0]);
126 }
127 for (int i = 0; i < eccLength; ++i)
128 data[eccOffset + i * stride] = ecc[eccLength - 1 - i];
129}
130
131/**
132* Creates the ECC200 error correction for an encoded message.
133*
134* @param codewords the codewords
135* @param symbolInfo information about the symbol to be encoded
136* @return the codewords with interleaved error correction.
137*/
138void
139ECEncoder::EncodeECC200(ByteArray& codewords, const SymbolInfo& symbolInfo)
140{
141 if (codewords.size() != (size_t)symbolInfo.dataCapacity()) {
142 throw std::invalid_argument("The number of codewords does not match the selected symbol");
143 }
144 codewords.resize(symbolInfo.codewordCount(), 0);
145 int blockCount = symbolInfo.interleavedBlockCount();
146 if (blockCount == 1) {
147 CreateECCBlock(codewords, 0, symbolInfo.dataCapacity(), symbolInfo.dataCapacity(), symbolInfo.errorCodewords(), 1);
148 }
149 else {
150 for (int block = 0; block < blockCount; block++)
151 CreateECCBlock(codewords, block, symbolInfo.dataLengthForInterleavedBlock(block + 1),
152 symbolInfo.dataCapacity() + block, symbolInfo.errorLengthForInterleavedBlock(), blockCount);
153 }
154}
